title._content: Brigadier General Clarence S. ""Bill"" Irvine Special Collection Photo

description._content: Catalog #: 09_01897 Title: Brigadier General Clarence S. ""Bill"" Irvine Special Collection Photo Additional Information: Ceremony to present the Distinguished Service Cross. Handwritten inscription ""The presentation of the D.S.C to Lt. Kelly - all these known pictures taken because of said presentation - aerial parade and review also. 1. Governor Samuel Stinson. 2. Gen. Lassater. 3. Lt. Kelly (who made first non-stop flight New York to Los Angeles) 4. Brig. Gen. Holhook. 5. Capt. Bush (adj to Sameul)"", Brigadier General Clarence Irvine enjoyed a long distinguished military career, mainly involving engineering. He served with the XXI Bomber Command (B-29's) during WWII and continued to serve throughout the 1950s and 1960s. Tags: Brigadier General Clarence S. ""Bill"" Irvine Special Collection Photo Repository: San Diego Air and Space Museum Archive
